AI-powered incident response / alert management system architecture. 

---

🔷 What this system is doing (in one line)

👉 It collects alerts from different systems, processes them using AI, and automatically helps resolve incidents or assist engineers.


---

🔶 Step-by-step flow

1. Sources (Where alerts come from)

Applications

APM Logs

Security/Infra alerts


➡️ These generate exceptions/alerts


---

2. Event Bus / Webhook Gateway

Acts as a central entry point

Collects all incoming alerts and forwards them



---

3. Ingest & Normalize Alerts

Converts different alert formats into a standard structure

Makes data consistent for further processing



---

4. Enrich with Context

Adds extra info like:

Past incidents

System metadata

Dependencies



👉 This makes alerts smarter and more meaningful


---

5. Prioritize & Deduplicate

Removes duplicate alerts

Assigns priority (critical / high / low)


👉 Prevents alert noise and overload


---

6. Run Playbooks (Core Engine)

This is the main AI-driven decision layer

It:

Decides what action to take

Runs automated workflows (playbooks)



---

🔶 Actions triggered from Playbooks

🛠️ Automation & Updates

Auto ticket updates

Status assignment

Incident ownership


🔔 Notifications

Slack / Email alerts


📊 Storage & Learning

Stores outcomes in DB

Improves future decisions (learning loop)



---

🔶 Supporting Tools (Right side)

Log Search Tool → helps in root cause analysis

JIRA Tool → ticketing

Metrics DB → stores system data

Rules Engine → policy-based decisions

Code Search Tool (GitHub) → find related code issues

Knowledge Base Tool → past solutions



---

🔶 Outputs (What user gets)

Actionable alert feed

Root cause hints

Reference links

JIRA tickets

Escalations

Analytics & drift signals



---

🔷 In short (easy explanation)

👉 “We are building a system that automatically handles production alerts using AI — it reduces noise, finds root causes, triggers actions, and helps engineers resolve issues faster.”


---

💡 Real-world meaning

Instead of engineers manually:

Checking logs

Creating tickets

Investigating issues


👉 This system does most of it automatically or assists intelligently


